## Executive Overview

The NEO THERMAL NODE represents the second pillar of the NEO Tri-Node Architecture and serves as the primary thermal intelligence layer within the PI220 ecosystem.

Historically, thermal energy has been treated as a byproduct of operation:

* Engine heat
* Electrical heat
* Aerodynamic heating
* Friction losses

Traditional systems focus on removing heat.

The NEO THERMAL NODE introduces a different philosophy:

> Heat is not waste.

> Heat is a recoverable resource.

The objective is to capture, govern, redistribute, and repurpose thermal energy across aerospace systems while simultaneously protecting structural integrity and increasing operational efficiency.

The NEO THERMAL NODE eventually becomes a core subsystem within:

* STARFRAME SF-1
* Boeing 220-X
* Boeing 220-Y
* Boeing 220-G Lattice Core
* Boeing 220-G Global

